  offerDialogue:
    name: Professor Bhan
    sentences:
    - Ah, you must be the new engineer the guild sent over! Welcome, welcome! Come
      in, don't just stand in the doorway.
    - I am Professor Bhan. I oversee all the major infrastructure and bridge contracts
      around these parts.
    - I hear you're looking for work. I actually have a ravine that desperately needs
      a crossing, but I can't just hand the job to a rookie without making sure you
      know your physics.
    - 'Before we talk business, you are going to need the holy grail of our profession:
      The Engineering Almanac.'
    - I left a spare copy on the table right over there. Go grab it, flip through
      it, and then come talk to me. We'll get you started on your first official
      contract!
  reminderDialogue:
    name: Professor Bhan
    sentences:
    - Ah, excellent! You have it. Treat that book well
    - Now, down to business. The local merchants desperately need a supply route
      across the eastern ravine.
    - I am authorizing your first official contract. We have a strict budget, and
      a heavy cargo vehicle is already waiting to cross..
    - Come on, let's go outside for your first contract. The build site is just down
      the path!
  finishedContractDialogue:
    name: 
    sentences: []
